wikipedia_page.main: James Reid (8 March 1875 – 19 March 1957) was a British sport shooter who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics. In 1912 he won the silver medal with the British team in the team military rifle competition. In the 600 metre free rifle event he finished 13th.
